you must obtain legally yourself. Nothing here circumvents any technical protection measure.

Provenance
----------
The mechanisms documented here were derived by reverse-engineering a single, legally-obtained copy of
the en-US 1.12.1 client through disassembly and differential testing against that binary. No leaked,
third-party-decompiled, or otherwise unauthorized source was used. Claims are presented as VERIFIED
against the binary, or labelled where they are inferred.

AI assistance
-------------
An AI assistant was used to help transcribe and cross-check the client's behaviour against the binary.
Every claim was gated by an objective differential test (transcribed code executed against the
original under emulation and compared output-for-output); the arbiter of correctness is the binary,
not the model. AI output was not accepted on trust.

